@node intro " MiXeRz -- INTRODUCTION -- "

 With various scripts that I've done to constantly improve Daydream BBS and
make the best of it, "The MiXeRz Collection" is the next step to an ever
changing BBS.

 "The MiXeRz Collection" includes three scripts :

( mXm.dd ) -- > MeNuMiXeR -- > for main menu

( bXm.dd ) -- > BaNNeRmIxEr -- > for log on banner

( gXm.dd ) -- > DiSmIxEr -- > for disconnect banner

Each of these three files changes an ANSI to another everytime a user comes
to see it.

ie, with bXm.dd, everytime a user logs on, the banner changes.





         @{"Introduction" Link intro}@{"Installation" Link install}@{"Known Bugs" Link bugs}@{"Future MiXz Releases" Link future}
      @{"Author" Link Me}@{"Other Releases" Link other}@{"Special thanks" Link thanku}@{"Contact Address" Link contact}@{"Conclusion" Link konk}

@endnode

@node Install " MiXeRz -- INSTALLATION -- "

 Before you attempt to install anything, make :

Three new banners (Banner.A, Banner.B, Banner.C)
Three new menus (Commands.A, Commands.B, Commands.C)
Three new logoff screens (Goodbye.A, Goodbye.B, Goodbye.C)

All these files should be placed in your display/iso directory.

Copy the three scripts to your DOORS: directory

Now, on with the real installation .

BANNER MIXER :

Open a text editor (ie, CygnusEd) and type the following lines :

˙G
˙DDoors:Rexx %N Doors:bxm.dd||

Save the file as Banner.GFX (Overwrite the original file)


LOGOFF BANNER MIXER :


Open a text editor (ie, CygnusEd) and type the following lines :

˙G
˙DDoors:Rexx %N Doors:gxm.dd||

Save the file as goodbye.GFX (Overwrite the original file)


MENU MIXER :

This is a bit tough.

Add the following lines to your Welcome.GFX file :

˙G
˙DDoors:Rexx %N Doors:mxm.dd||

Save the file.

Open the Script (mxm.dd) in the text editor, and alter the location of the
menus according to the directory which has the menus is located.

ie, your conference is in a directory called FRY:, then replace all ICE:
with FRY: ... And make sure the menus (commands.A .... ) are in that
conference's directory (ie, FRY:display/iso/)




